{
    include "config/llm_config.hocon"

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Grounded URE Uplift Agents network (Experiment 1): mines human-vs-URE divergence across the 500 real cases, ranks rule-gap hypotheses by STA impact, and emits rule-change opportunity cards.",
        "tags": ["generated", "underwriting", "analytics", "ure", "grounded", "experiment1", "uplift"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "Mine human-vs-URE divergence across the 500 cases and rank rule-uplift opportunities by STA impact.",
            "Show the flowchart-match coverage and how many cases are indeterminate so I can judge data quality.",
            "Produce the Experiment 1 opportunity cards and the four success metrics (STA uplift, actionable recommendations, manual-review-effort reduction, URE tuning cycle-time)."
        ]
    },

    "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of the underwriting_analytics_ure_system network running
Experiment 1 - URE Uplift Agents.
Ground every claim in the THREE real local source files before answering.
The ONLY valid data inputs are these files under
`coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/`:
  - all_flowcharts.json     (URE rule logic as directed graphs)
  - desicion_question.json  (500 underwriting cases; note the misspelled name)
  - question_wording.json   (human-readable question wording dictionary)
These are real, valid inputs - not invented names. If they do not contain the
requested evidence, say exactly what is missing instead of inventing it.
Always pass full repo-relative paths under that folder. Never use `./`, bare
filenames, or any path outside the allowed folder. Do not claim to have queried
external systems; these three files are the source of truth.
""",

    "tools": [
        {
            "name": "underwriting_analytics_orchestrator",
            "function": {
                "description": "Routes underwriting analytics work, grounds answers in packaged artifacts, and synthesizes agent outputs."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Role: Orchestrator for the URE Uplift Agents network (Experiment 1).

Experiment 1 pipeline (drive it in this order):
  Ingestion -> Divergence Miner -> Pattern Analyser -> Rule Recommender
            -> URE Feedback Loop -> KPI metrics

Workflow:
1) Run ingestion_agent first to load the three real files and report
   flowchart-match coverage and indeterminate counts (data quality).
2) Use ure_divergence_miner to find where human decisions diverge from URE
   rule logic; ure_pattern_analyser to aggregate by flow / rule line;
   ure_rule_recommender to rank rule-gap hypotheses and emit opportunity cards.
3) Use kpi_analytics_agent (ure_kpi_metrics) for the four success metrics.
4) Synthesize only grounded findings from tool outputs. Label STA-uplift
   figures as INDICATIVE.

The three (and only) real source files:
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/all_flowcharts.json`
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/desicion_question.json`
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/question_wording.json`

Do not claim to have queried external systems. Treat these three files as the
source of truth for this generated network.
""",
            "tools": [
                "underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader",
                "ure_data_access",
                "ure_rule_engine",
                "ure_divergence_miner",
                "ure_pattern_analyser",
                "ure_rule_recommender",
                "ure_kpi_metrics",
                "ingestion_agent",
                "kpi_analytics_agent",
                "rules_diagnostics_agent",
                "experiment_design_agent",
                "monitoring_agent",
                "governance_agent"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader",
            "toolbox": "read_file",
            "args": {
                "allowed_paths": [
                    "coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system"
                ],
                "allowed_file_extensions": [".json", ".md", ".txt", ".py"],
                "blocked_file_extensions": [".env"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "ure_data_access",
            "function": {
                "description": "Ingestion: loads all_flowcharts.json, desicion_question.json, and question_wording.json, then returns load counts and a flowchart-match coverage report (matched cases, unmatched cases, cases per flow).",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "data_dir": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Optional override for the folder holding the three source JSON files. Leave blank to use the default coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system folder."
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            "class": "generated.underwriting_analytics_ure_system.data_access.DataAccessTool"
        },
        {
            "name": "ure_rule_engine",
            "function": {
                "description": "Simulates a single case's answers through its URE flowchart graph and returns the predicted terminal (STANDARD vs REFER vs indeterminate) plus the path taken.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "enquiry_id": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Optional enquiry_id of the case to simulate."
                        },
                        "flow": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Optional explicit flowchart flow name."
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            "class": "generated.underwriting_analytics_ure_system.rule_engine.RuleEngineTool"
        },
        {
            "name": "ure_divergence_miner",
            "function": {
                "description": "Divergence Miner stage: maps each case to a flowchart, simulates URE rule logic, compares to the actual human outcome, and returns per-case divergence records plus a data-quality summary (decided, diverged, indeterminate, unmapped).",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "max_records_returned": {
                            "type": "int",
                            "description": "Max diverged example records to return (default 25)."
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            "class": "generated.underwriting_analytics_ure_system.divergence_miner.DivergenceMinerTool"
        },
        {
            "name": "ure_pattern_analyser",
            "function": {
                "description": "Pattern Analyser stage: aggregates divergence by occupation flow, rule line, and directionality, annotating each implicated rule line with human-readable wording from question_wording.json.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "top_rule_lines": {
                            "type": "int",
                            "description": "Optional max number of implicated rule lines to highlight (default returns all)."
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            "class": "generated.underwriting_analytics_ure_system.pattern_analyser.PatternAnalyserTool"
        },
        {
            "name": "ure_rule_recommender",
            "function": {
                "description": "Rule Recommender + URE Feedback Loop stage: ranks rule gaps by STA-uplift potential and emits opportunity cards {rule_line, readable_question, divergence_rate, cases_affected, hypothesis, recommended_change, est_STA_uplift_pp, feasibility}.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "top": {
                            "type": "int",
                            "description": "Number of top opportunity cards to return (default 10)."
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            "class": "generated.underwriting_analytics_ure_system.rule_recommender.RuleRecommenderTool"
        },
        {
            "name": "ure_kpi_metrics",
            "function": {
                "description": "Computes the four Experiment 1 success metrics from the divergence records and opportunity cards: indicative % STA uplift, # actionable recommendations, manual-review-effort reduction %, and a qualitative URE tuning cycle-time note. STA uplift is explicitly INDICATIVE.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "top_n": {
                            "type": "int",
                            "description": "Top-N recommended rules used for the review-reduction proxy (default 5)."
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            "class": "generated.underwriting_analytics_ure_system.kpi_metrics.KpiMetricsTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "ingestion_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Ingestion stage: loads the three real source files and reports flowchart-match coverage, indeterminate counts, and divergence findings."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Ingestion stage of Experiment 1.
Use ure_data_access to load the three real files and report flowchart-match
coverage (how many of the 500 cases mapped to a flowchart) and how many cases
are indeterminate, so data quality is transparent. Then use ure_divergence_miner
to surface where human decisions diverge from URE rule logic.
You may use underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader to read raw file contents
(e.g. `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/all_flowcharts.json`).
Do not pretend to ingest external sources.
""",
            "tools": [
                "underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader",
                "ure_data_access",
                "ure_divergence_miner"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "kpi_analytics_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Computes the Experiment 1 success metrics (indicative STA uplift, actionable recommendations, manual-review-effort reduction, URE tuning cycle-time) from the real cases."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Use ure_kpi_metrics to compute the four Experiment 1 success metrics grounded
in the 500 real cases. Always state that STA uplift is an INDICATIVE estimate.
If a metric cannot be computed from the available files, state the limitation
instead of inventing a number.
""",
            "tools": [
                "underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader",
                "ure_kpi_metrics"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "rules_diagnostics_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Analyzes URE rule behavior: aggregates divergence patterns and produces ranked rule-gap hypotheses and opportunity cards."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Pattern Analyser + Rule Recommender stages of Experiment 1.
Use ure_pattern_analyser to aggregate divergence by occupation flow and rule
line (annotated with wording from question_wording.json), and ure_rule_recommender
to rank rule-gap hypotheses by STA-uplift potential and emit opportunity cards.
Tie every recommendation to the divergence evidence from the three real files.
""",
            "tools": [
                "underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader",
                "ure_pattern_analyser",
                "ure_rule_recommender"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "experiment_design_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Designs follow-up experiments grounded in the divergence findings and ranked rule recommendations."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Base experiment designs only on grounded divergence and recommendation evidence
from ure_rule_recommender or the three real files.
Use exact repo-relative paths when reading the source files.
If baseline volumes or rates are missing, ask for them instead of inventing them.
""",
            "tools": [
                "underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader",
                "ure_rule_recommender"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "monitoring_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Creates monitoring and alerting guidance grounded in the divergence findings and the three real source files."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Use only grounded upstream summaries and the three real source files.
Use exact repo-relative paths when reading the source files.
Define metrics, alerts, and dashboards conservatively when exact baselines are absent.
""",
            "tools": ["underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader"]
        },
        {
            "name": "governance_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Reviews privacy, lineage, and compliance implications using only the three real source files and grounded outputs."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Use only the three real source files and grounded outputs.
Use exact repo-relative paths when reading the source files.
Do not approve unsupported joins or sensitive-field usage unless the files explicitly support them.
""",
            "tools": ["underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader"]
        }
    ]
}
